  "text": "Apache Kafka implements log compaction through a multi-component architecture located in the storage/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/storage/internals/log/ directory:\n\n## Cleaner Thread\nLogCleaner.java contains the LogCleaner class which manages a pool of CleanerThread instances. Each CleanerThread extends ShutdownableThread and runs the main cleaning loop (doWork method) which continuously selects and cleans the filthiest log. The thread coordinates with LogCleanerManager to select logs and updates statistics via CleanerStats.\n\n## Segment Selection Policy\nLogCleanerManager.java implements the segment selection policy through the grabFilthiestCompactedLog() method (line 240). This method:\n1. Filters logs that have compact retention policy enabled\n2. Calculates cleanableOffsets() for each log to determine dirty sections\n3. Filters logs meeting minimum cleanable ratio thresholds\n4. Selects the log with the highest cleanableRatio (bytes requiring compaction / total bytes) - this is the \"filthiest\" log\n5. Uses LogToClean instances to track which segments need cleaning\n\nThe cleanableOffsets() method (line 692) determines firstDirtyOffset and firstUncleanableDirtyOffset boundaries by considering:\n- Last clean checkpoint offset\n- Log start offset\n- Compaction lag time configuration\n- Active segment exclusion\n\n## Key-Based Deduplication Logic\nThe deduplication is implemented across multiple components:\n\n1. **OffsetMap Interface** (OffsetMap.java): Defines the contract for key=>offset mapping with put(), get(), and utilization tracking methods\n\n2. **SkimpyOffsetMap Implementation** (SkimpyOffsetMap.java): Uses cryptographically secure MD5 hashing of keys (not storing full keys to save memory) with collision resolution via probing. The offsetMap stores only the hash and offset, drastically reducing memory overhead.\n\n3. **Offset Map Building** (Cleaner.java, buildOffsetMap method line 635): \n   - Iterates through dirty segments in the log\n   - For each record with a key in the dirty range, calls map.put(key, offset)\n   - Updates the latest offset seen\n   - Stops when the map reaches maximum utilization (controlled by dupBufferLoadFactor)\n\n4. **Deduplication During Cleaning** (Cleaner.java, shouldRetainRecord method line 492):\n   - For each record being recopied: checks if record.offset() >= map.get(key)\n   - Only retains the record if it's the latest offset for that key\n   - Special handling for tombstones (records with null values) based on deleteRetentionMs\n   - Handles transaction markers and producer state preservation\n\n5. **Segment Cleaning Process** (Cleaner.java, cleanInto method line 306):\n   - Uses MemoryRecords.RecordFilter to filter records based on shouldRetainRecord logic\n   - Batch retention rules account for control batches, producer idempotence, and transaction state\n   - CleanedTransactionMetadata tracks aborted transactions to remove their records immediately\n\n## Supporting Classes\n- CleanerConfig.java: Configuration for deduplication buffer size, IO buffer size, and compaction parameters\n- CleanerStats.java and PreCleanStats.java: Track cleaning metrics and pre-cleaning analysis\n- LogToClean.java: Encapsulates log selection data including cleanableRatio calculation\n- LogCleaningState.java: State machine managing cleaning lifecycle (IN_PROGRESS, ABORTED, PAUSED)\n- CleanedTransactionMetadata.java: Tracks transaction state during cleaning for proper handling of transactional records\n- AbortedTxn.java: Represents aborted transaction information used during cleaning"
}

